{
  "texts": [
    "To quantitatively evaluate our models, we used BLEU score 26, which is a commonly used metric for machine translation.",
    "BLEU score compares the output of a machine translation system against human (reference) translations, with a higher score indicating greater correspondence.",
    "It calculates n-gram precision between the candidate and reference translations, along with a brevity penalty for shorter output.",
    "BLEU score provides an automated way to evaluate translation quality and has been shown to correlate well with human judgements.",
    "Consequently, we report BLEU scores to compare the performance of our different models."
  ]
}